pibKbpLwIe2BuUIQ13Hc8vEXQ1RXZgc67sUIwpv2y_NgL7o5hIF4KdQl6IT8adeyS19O-g==\",\"summary\":[]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 uses the normal Vert.x WebClient pattern and can be meaningfully tested with an embedded Vert.x HTTP server, without Docker or extra Maven dependencies. However, the resolved Vert.x 5.0.1 stack pulls Netty 4.2.2.Final, and the existing 5.0.0 test scaffold already documents that Netty 4.2.x needs explicit unsafe-access runtime properties for Java 25 native-image runs; the current condition only applies to 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Configure the native test runtime for 5.0.1, or generally for Vert.x 5 / Netty 4.2.x, with system properties: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. Meaningful tests should use Vertx.vertx(), WebClient/WebClientSession/CachingWebClient, and an in-process Vert.x HttpServer on localhost rather than relying on external network services.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If tests exercise POJO JSON mapping through Jackson databind-specific paths, jackson-databind is optional in vertx-core and may need deliberate dependency handling; JsonObject/Buffer/String BodyCodec paths do not require that extra dependency.\",\n    \"The issue is a native-image runtime failure, so local Gradle/native-image verification remains authoritative for whether the Netty Java 25 runtime properties fully resolve the failure.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d8228471a2c71e8016a3eec17bc7c8195851aee473bc573d4\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 762, "output": 852, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25678, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782508557422, "responseId": "resp_0d822847